HEADWORD: Conviviality
<hw>Con*viv`i*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Convivialities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>
<def>The good humor or mirth indulged in upon festive occasions; a
convivial spirit or humor; festivity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

